        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "First prepare z up. Send a beam through a z analyzer and keep only the upper output. A second z measurement would now return up with certainty.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "filter"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 6,
      "narration_text": "How can a sideways measurement destroy that certainty without applying a random classical kick?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.04,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The state z up is not definite along x. In the x basis it is an equal superposition of x plus and x minus.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "split"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.62,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "An x measurement therefore produces x plus or x minus with equal probability. The measurement prepares whichever x eigenstate its outcome reports.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "branch"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.32,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Take the x plus branch. Relative to z, x plus is an equal superposition of z up and z down. A final z analyzer must split it fifty-fifty.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "split"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.54,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The x minus branch also gives equal z probabilities. So whether you condition on either x result or forget which x result occurred, the final z statistics are half up and half down.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "merge"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.24,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Compare the sequences. Z followed directly by Z gives one hundred percent up. Z, then X, then Z gives fifty percent up and fifty percent down.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.85,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The middle measurement does not reveal a hidden sideways value while preserving z. It changes the state into an x eigenstate, which has no definite z value.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "qualify"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.39,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Measurement order matters because spin components along different axes are incompatible observables. Certainty in one basis becomes superposition in the other.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "map"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.6,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Rotate the middle analyzer gradually. At zero degrees, z certainty survives. At ninety degrees, the final z result is maximally randomized. Intermediate angles interpolate smoothly.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "scan"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.71,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:48:10"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Z up was certain. X made a new state. The last Z measurement reveals the lost compatibility as a fifty-fifty split.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.27,
